    <stitle>AFC 98902 - 9300 Model Frame/Ride Improvement</stitle>
    <afc id="afc98902">
        <afcnum>98902</afcnum>
        <afcdate>May, 1998</afcdate>
        <subjectfile>FRAME</subjectfile>
        <subject>9300 Model Frame/Ride Improvement</subject>
        <apply>
            <configure>
                <truckmodelgroup/>

                <truckmodel>9300
                    <daterange>
                        <startdate>05/01/1997</startdate>
                        <enddate>11/13/1997</enddate>
                    </daterange>
                </truckmodel>
            </configure>
        </apply>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>This AFC applies to 9300 Pro Sleeper Models with CabMate air suspension, behind the cab fuel tank,
                    234 inch or longer wheelbase and built between May 1, 1997 and November 13, 1997.
                </para>
                <para>9300 Pro Sleeper Models with CabMate air suspension, behind the cab fuel tank, 234 inch or longer
                    wheelbase and built between May 1, 1997 and November 13, 1997 may not provide expected ride quality
                    on concrete highway surfaces characterized as having uneven divider or expansion joints.
                </para>
                <para>To improve the ride quality for this condition, it is recommended that a frame tie be installed on
                    the chassis frame under the clutch housing.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
