        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="2">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate bracket, Part Number 423698C1, mounting hole centerlines 16-1/2 inches behind the
                    front axle suspension rear spring shackle bracket bottom flange bolt on both frame rails (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9890201">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f9890201" figsize="pwide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g9890201.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Locate Bracket Mounting Hole Centerlines 16-1/2 Inches Behind Flange Bolt</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using the new frame tie bracket as a guide, hold it up to the lower frame flange and
                    mark the hole location and drill two holes per frame rail to accept 5/8 inch bolts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Mount bracket, Part Number 423698C1, to each frame rail with bolts, Part Number 414077C1
                    (5/8-18UNF x 1-3/4), and nuts, Part Number 414089C1. Tighten to 160 to 175 ft-lbs. (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9890202">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f9890202" figsize="pwide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g9890202.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Mount Bracket to Each Frame Rail and Install Frame Tie Tube</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install frame tie tube, Part Number 530771C1, to the bracket with bolts, Part Number
                    414078C1 (5/8-UNF x 2), and nuts, Part Number 414089C1. Tighten to 160 to 175 ft-lbs. (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f9890202">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
